Thank you to everyone who reached out to wish me a happy birthday! 
Sharing a birthday celebration with my best friend @oliviawong21 is such a gift! So many more photos to share soon 🫶
I also have to shoutout @tayrosew for making me the cutest little Pisces GLUTEN FREE cake I’ve ever seen. Easily my favorite cake I’ve ever been given! 
And the biggest thank you to my best friend @6allyssa for not only picking me up from the airport at 2:30am Sunday night but also putting together my gallery wall in my bedroom and framing everything for me, because she knew I absolutely did not want to do it! You get me 💓

It’s a wrap on our Hollywood Invitational 2023! I can’t even begin to express the gratitude that I feel to be a part of this team and to be able to work alongside these humans. Being a part of @hollywooddancejamz for the last 8 years has been one of the greatest blessings of my life. Growing into the dancer, choreographer, educator, and person I am today within the warm embrace of this company. Being able to watch these kids grow up, learn, change, and blossom is truly one of the greatest privileges. To be a part of their journeys is something I’ll never take for granted. Proud doesn’t even begin to cover it! My heart is overflowing. Cheers to an incredible week 🤍

15 year old Myranda had dreams of moving to LA to be a dancer. She didn’t dream of dancing for the biggest artists or in the biggest movies. The #1 thing on her list of dreams was to dance in a burlesque show in Hollywood. 
Nearly 10 years later, we take our final bow for On the Fringe. To have been a principal cast dancer in this sensational show in such a notable venue with the most special and incredible dancers, I couldn’t have dreamt a better dream if I tried.
Thank you @tracyphillips66 for this extraordinary opportunity to perform, learn, grow, and share. Thank you to @catch.her.in.the.rye @niccomarcantonio , @delilahrose2023  for the love, support, and each of their incredible contributions to this show. Thank you for taking such good care of us every Saturday and all of the days in between. 
And to the girls, it’s been an honor and a privilege to dance on this stage with you these past two years. This has been a time in my life I will never forget. Learning from you all, and from my own journey within and during the time of this show has made strides for myself and my femininity, strength, bravery, vulnerability, and sensuality. I wouldn’t be the woman, mover, dancer, or performer I am today without Fringe. Thank you forever Fringe! You will so dearly missed. ❤️

I had the pleasure and honor of being a choreographer as well as a dancer this season on @miraquienbaila One of my favorite pieces and memories from the show was this number I got to choreograph and perform with @adrian_lastra Adrían, your heart, trust, commitment, vulnerability, strength, and bravery were all more than I could have asked for. Thank you for going there with me. Thank you for your constant hard work and dedication and willingness to try something new and going for it 100%. Eres un bailarín!! 
Thank you to my friends and peers for their input, contributions, love and support during this week and all of the other weeks on the show. And a shoutout to @marcquet13 for your energy in the room and for all of your help and support for both Adrían and myself. ✨#miraquienbaila
